1. How to start the app:
    a. in a new Linux terminal:
        docker-compose rm && docker-compose up
        (and wait for "database ready to accept connections")

    b. In another new Linux terminal: npm run start-dev-server

2. How to test the app:
    npm run test

3. How to run a single test:
    jest --config jest.unit.config.js $MY_FIRST_FAILING_TEST_PATH"

4. How to run the unit tests:
    npm run test:unit

5. How to run the integration tests:
    npm run test:integration

6. Completely destroy the postgres database and rebuild it:
    docker-compose rm -sf
    docker-compose up

7. Populate the database with example data used for debugging:
    a. First start the docker containers:
        docker-compose rm && docker-compose up
    b. Populate the message_db database:
        npm run populate
    c. In pgadmin (see below on how to start it) you open/create message_db server and then visualise the table in the message_store schema;

8. connect to pgadmin: open browser to localhost:5050/browser and use:
    uid: admin@admin.com
    pwd: root

